&
 A
  ar[d]^*+{f}

\
 B
  ar[r]_*+{g}
&
 C
}end{xy}$

such that $f circ p_1 = g circ p_2$, subject to the following UMP:


:For any commutative diagram:

:::$begin{xy}xymatrix{
 Q
  ar[r]^*+{q_1}
  ar[d]_*+{q_2}
&
 A
  ar[d]^*+{f}

\
 B
  ar[r]_*+{g}
&
 C
}end{xy}$

:there is a unique morphism $u: Q to P$ making the following diagram commute:

:::$begin{xy}xymatrix@+1em{
 Q
  ar@/^/[rrd]^*+{q_1}
  ar@/_/[ddr]_*+{q_2}
  ar@{-->}[rd]^*+{u}

\
&
 P
  ar[r]_*+{p_1}
  ar[d]^*+{p_2}
&
 A
  ar[d]^*+{f}

\
&
 B
  ar[r]_*+{g}
&
 C
